The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for multi-resource allocation in smart city applications, where agents are constrained by communication infrastructure and privacy considerations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category, which deals with the interaction and coordination of multiple agents. The paper also involves resource allocation, which is a topic covered in the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. Additionally, the use of communication infrastructure implies that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper proposes a distributed algorithm, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper involves the allocation of shared resources, which could also fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
